name: SVGFilterElement
description: The SVGFilterElement interface provides access to the properties of <filter> elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

members.name: SVGFilterElement.filterUnits
members.description: An SVGAnimatedEnumeration that corresponds to the filterUnits attribute of the given <filter> element. Takes one of the constants defined in SVGUnitTypes.

members.name: SVGFilterElement.primitiveUnits
members.description: An SVGAnimatedEnumeration that corresponds to the primitiveUnits attribute of the given <filter> element. Takes one of the constants defined in SVGUnitTypes.

members.name: SVGFilterElement.x
members.description: An SVGAnimatedLength that corresponds to the x attribute on the given <filter> element.

members.name: SVGFilterElement.y
members.description: An SVGAnimatedLength that corresponds to the y attribute of the given <filter> element.

members.name: SVGFilterElement.width
members.description: An SVGAnimatedLength that corresponds to the width attribute of the given <filter> element.

members.name: SVGFilterElement.height
members.description: An SVGAnimatedLength that corresponds to the height attribute of the given <filter> element.

members.name: SVGFilterElement.filterResX
members.description: An SVGAnimatedInteger that contains the X component of the filterRes attribute of the given <filter> element.

members.name: SVGFilterElement.filterResY
members.description: An SVGAnimatedInteger that contains the Y component of the filterRes attribute of the given <filter> element.

members.name: SVGFilterElement.setFilterRes()
members.description: Sets the values of the filterRes attribute.
